{"type":"message","id":"e53261af","parentId":"7445a8e5","timestamp":"2026-06-11T09:37:05.282Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have npm and python (Windows Store Python, which might be limited). Let me try using the well-known wxappUnpacker tool.\n\nThere are a few tools for unpacking wxapkg:\n1. **wxappUnpacker** - https://github.com/poer/wxappUnpacker (requires node, uses `babel` to transpile)\n2. **unwxapkg** - simpler, just extracts raw files\n3. **WeChatMsg** - has wxapkg tool\n4. **cui-utils/pc_wxapkg_decrypt** - for PC version\n\nModern wxapkg files from PC/Desktop WeChat have different encryption compared to old mobile versions. The tool might need to handle the \"gzip first then XOR with first 5 bytes\" format.\n\nLet me try the `wxappUnpacker` approach first. But actually, for a simpler approach, let me try a node-based unpacker.\n\nLet me look for available packages or tools already installed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_W2np3yjDqFOJc9FTnDe63020","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"npm ls -g --depth=0 2>&1","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_lx6K6IQSN8Ku8ocTfrOg2310","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python --version 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":142,"output":334,"cacheRead":16128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16604,"cost":{"input":0.000019880000000000003,"output":0.00009352000000000001,"cacheRead":0.000451584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000564984}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781170620447,"responseId":"8b926c26-8c89-40e6-aba8-1b487fb8d702"}}
