{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6d9c2b80bca4b3be68d1bc5b80c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"sender\": \"Yousan(叶枝君)\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-06-11 17:56 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Yousan(叶枝君) (ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"name\": \"Yousan(叶枝君)\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"336dfe64","parentId":"515af5da","timestamp":"2026-06-11T09:56:41.114Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"c63b76dc","parentId":"336dfe64","timestamp":"2026-06-11T09:56:48.139Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the token expiration time. Let me look at the source code to find if there's any info about token expiry.\n\nFrom the code I've already analyzed:\n- The token is stored in `wx.getStorageSync(\"go_chess.token\")` and set via `d(e)` (which is the `setToken` function that sets `i.Authorization = e`)\n- The app calls `this.login()` on every `onLaunch` (i.e., every time the mini program starts)\n\nSo it re-logins (and refreshes the token) every time the app launches. But I should look for any specific expiration logic, refresh token mechanism, or stored expiry time.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_MnYMjjJNTRJ7cpTZXWco6269","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"const fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst root = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\Downloads\\\\小程序解包\\\\涨棋网';\nconst fp = path.join(root, 'app-service.js');\nconst content = fs.readFileSync(fp, 'utf8');\n\n// Search for token expiry\nconst keywords = ['expire', 'expiry', 'exp', 'refresh', 'tokenExp', 'ttl', '时效', '有效期'];\nfor (const kw of keywords) {\n  const idx = content.indexOf(kw);\n  if (idx >= 0) {\n    console.log(`=== Found \"${kw}\" at offset ${idx} ===`);\n    const start = Math.max(0, idx - 100);\n    const end = Math.min(content.length, idx + 300);\n    console.log(content.substring(start, end));\n    console.log();\n  }\n}\n\n// Also look at the login handler - what does onUserLogin do?\nconst loginIdx = content.indexOf('onUserLogin');\nif (loginIdx >= 0) {\n  console.log('=== onUserLogin handler ===');\n  const start = Math.max(0, loginIdx - 50);\n  const end = Math.min(content.length, loginIdx + 1000);\n  console.log(content.substring(start, end));\n}\n\n// Search for Authorization header usage - where token is checked\nconst authIdx = content.indexOf('Authorization');\nif (authIdx >= 0) {\n  console.log('\\n=== Authorization header handling ===');\n  const start = Math.max(0, authIdx - 50);\n  const end = Math.min(content.length, authIdx + 400);\n  console.log(content.substring(start, end));\n}\n\n// Check app.js for the login response handling\nconsole.log('\\n=== Login response handling ===');\nconst loginRespPattern = content.match(/onUserLogin\\s*=\\s*function[^}]+/);\nif (loginRespPattern) {\n  console.log(loginRespPattern[0].substring(0, 2000));\n}\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\find_expiry.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":13656,"output":643,"cacheRead":72064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86363,"cost":{"input":0.0019118400000000002,"output":0.00018004000000000002,"cacheRead":0.002017792,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004109672}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781171801115,"responseId":"09247d3f-fe6b-4fa6-915f-e2c14057c0d0"}}
