{"type":"message","id":"1ef5f9aa","parentId":"eef4b093","timestamp":"2026-06-11T09:56:58.211Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the code analysis:\n\n1. `onUserLogin` handler is called after login succeeds. Looking at the code, the token is stored with `d(e)` which is `setToken`:\n   ```javascript\n   function d(e) {\n     e ? (i.Authorization = e, wx.setStorageSync(\"go_chess.token\", e)) : \n          (delete i.Authorization, wx.removeStorageSync(\"go_chess.token\"))\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. The login is called every time the app launches (`onLaunch` calls `this.login()`). So the token might be refreshed on each app start.\n\n3. I found \"有效期\" (validity period) in the code but that's related to card/plan expiry, not token expiry.\n\n4. Looking at `refreshTastes` in user module - this might be a token refresh mechanism.\n\nLet me look more carefully at the user module to see if there's any token refresh or expiry logic.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_PaMJMVrWWMMLmfOQZlvg1128","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"const fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst root = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\Downloads\\\\小程序解包\\\\涨棋网';\nconst fp = path.join(root, 'app-service.js');\nconst content = fs.readFileSync(fp, 'utf8');\n\n// Find onUserLogin and onLoginFail full code\nconst userIdx = content.indexOf('onUserLogin');\nif (userIdx >= 0) {\n  // Find the full App block\n  const appBlock = content.substring(0, 200000); // First 200k chars should contain app.js\n  const appMatch = appBlock.match(/App\\(\\{[^]*?onUserLogin\\s*:\\s*function[^}]*?\\}/);\n  \n  // Try finding by keyword\n  const patterns = [\n    {name: 'onUserLogin', pat: /onUserLogin\\s*(:|=)\\s*function\\s*\\([^)]*\\)\\s*\\{[^}]*\\}[,)]?/},\n    {name: 'onLoginFail', pat: /onLoginFail\\s*(:|=)\\s*function\\s*\\([^)]*\\)\\s*\\{[^}]*\\}[,)]?/},\n    {name: 'refreshTastes', pat: /refreshTastes[^}]*\\}[^}]*\\}[^}]